#staging-deployment.yaml

This Kubernetes Deployment manifest is for the staging environment.
It specifies three replicas of the application.
Selector and labels ensure proper identification and association with the environment.
The container image tag is set to staging to differentiate it from the production deployment.
The application container exposes port 8080.



#production-deployment.yaml

This Kubernetes Deployment manifest is for the production environment.
It specifies five replicas of the application.
Selector and labels ensure proper identification and association with the environment.
The container image tag is set to latest, representing the latest production-ready version.
The application container exposes port 8080.
Remember to replace placeholders like your-app, your-container-image, and others with your actual application and image details. Adjust the replica counts, ports, and other configurations based on your application's requirements.